						               													<description>Battle for the First Panzer Army covers the breakout of the eponymous army from its position in Ukraine in the spring of 1944.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 21&amp;quot;x30&amp;quot; map (in four sections) has a scale of three miles per hex. There are over 200 counters; most units are regiments or divisions. There are fourteen turns of one day each (there is only one scenario).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The core systems are mostly standard. The Germans get an additional mechanized movement phase after combat. Combat itself is the most unusual aspect; the strength ratio determines not a column to roll on but a table, with the column in that table determined by troop quality and terrain. Troop quality has three levels and the highest-level units exert better zones of control than others.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
